Do men incur penalties of divorce by engaging in extra marital affairs outside of their marriages?

Mgbechi (1992) mentioned that “Immoral Character is not a reason for divorce.” Nature reminds men that the man does not have the soul of the woman, nor does the woman develop the soul of the man. In fact, the Bible says that God created man first and woman later, suggesting the fact that men are special beings. Most of them get lost thinking that they aren’t masculine enough, that they don’t have enough money, that they don’t have a clear future and so on. The reality is, the public has a strange opinion of these individuals, but you have the ability to change that through the small amount of money it takes to find a housewife.

There seems to be a preponderance of poor divorce cases in the country
